<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Monday on the New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Stock Market, 
and American Stock Exchange. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
	Firstar Corp. rose 5/16 to 30 3/8.  
</P>
<P>
	Mercantile Bancorp rose 3 11/16 to 60 11/16.  
</P>
<P>
	Firstar agreed to acquire Mercantile Bancorp. in a $9.9 billion  
stock swap late Friday. Mercantile shareholders would receive 2.091 
shares of Firstar stock for each of their shares. The share 
exchange, which values Mercantile shares at $66 apiece, represents 
a 29 percent premium over Mercantile's closing price Thursday at 
$51.25. 

</P>
<P>
	YPF Sociedad's American depositary receipts fell 1 3/16 to 42  
11/16. 
</P>
<P>
	Repsol SA, a Spanish oil, natural-gas and chemicals concern,  
made an all-cash offer Friday for the 85 percent of YPF, it doesn't 
already own. The offer values YPF, an Argentine oil and gas 
company, at $44.78 a share. 

</P>
<P>
	Circus Circus Enterprises Inc. rose 4 7/8 to 25 15/16.  
</P>
<P>
	The gaming and resort concern estimates first-quarter earnings  
of 40 cents to 42 cents a share, before one-time charges. Analysts 
had estimated earnings of 25 cents a share. 

</P>
<P>
	GP Strategies fell 6 1/8 to 9 1/4.  
</P>
<P>
	First-quarter earnings rose to 23 cents from 17 cents a year  
ago, but the company said second-quarter sales will fall below the 
company's earlier targets because of softer revenues from 
information technology training services. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
	VLSI Technology Inc., rose 1 7/8 to 20 3/4.  
</P>
<P>
	Royal Philips Electronics's American depositary receipts rose 3 1/8  
to 88 1/4 on the New York Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	Royal Philips will acquire VLSI, which designs and makes  
integrated computer circuits, in a deal worth $1 billion. Royal 
Philips, which already owns about 2.5 percent of VLSI, will pay $21 
a share, or $953 million, for the remaining shares. The agreement 
comes after more than two months of arduous pursuit by Royal 
Philips. On Feb. 26, Royal Philips offered $17 per share for VLSI. 

</P>
<P>
	Warp 10 Technologies Inc. rose 31/32 to 2 29/32.  
</P>
<P>
	IBM selected Warp's adsGallery.com Web site as a venue for its  
HotMedia product, an Internet technology designed to enhance the 
online display of products. adsGallery.com provides a directory of 
art agencies and art directors and features portfolios of 
advertising campaigns. 

</P>
<P>
	ABR Information Services Inc. rose 7 1/2 to 25.  
</P>
<P>
	Ceridian Corp., fell 1/2 to 36 1/8 on the New York Stock Exchange.  
</P>
<P>
	Ceridian agreed to acquire ABR, a healthcare benefits  
administrator, for about $750 million in cash, about $25.50 a 
share. 

</P>
<P>
	Marimba Inc. rose 6 1/4 to 67.  
</P>
<P>
	The shares have more than tripled since the company, which makes  
tools for updating software packages over the Internet, made an 
initial public offering Thursday at $20 apiece. Shares soared 
Friday to close at $60.75, as investors ignored operating losses 
and focused instead on the company's potential for Internet-related 
growth. 

</P>
