<HEADLINE> Server Outage Halts eBay Auctions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- All auctions on eBay were temporarily suspended  
Monday after the popular Internet site experienced a server outage 
and wasn't able to process any bids or accept new listings. 
</P>
<P>
	The auction company said the troubles began around 8:30 a.m. EDT  
and lasted until just before 2 p.m. EDT, although there were 
earlier reports of problems from some users. 
</P>
<P>
	Due to the outage, eBay couldn't host auctions of just-released  
merchandise tied to ``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace.'' 
By midday Monday, rival Amazon.com had more than 15 auctions of new 
toys and other products based on the much-awaited movie. 
</P>
<P>
	EBay said that all auctions that were scheduled to end during  
the shutdown or for one hour afterwards will be extended by 24 
hours. 
</P>
<P>
	``We are always concerned when we have any downtime on the  
site,'' said Kevin Pursglove, senior director for communications at 
eBay. ``We are trying to respond as quickly as we can.'' 
</P>
<P>
	On its online announcement board, eBay told customers who felt  
their auctions were ``materially impacted'' as a result of the 
outage to contact the company to get their fees refunded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
