<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 'Entrapment' Snares Big Audience / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ``Entrapment,'' starring Sean Connery and  
Catherine Zeta-Jones in a slick tale of thievery and duplicity, 
opened with a strong $20.1 million at the North American box 
office, final figures showed today. 
</P>
<P>
	But ``Idle Hands,'' the comic-horror story of a teen whose hand  
has a murderous mind of its own, debuted with a paltry $1.8 million 
for seventh place. 
</P>
<P>
	``The Matrix'' fell to second place with $8.7 million, followed  
by ``Life'' in third with $6.5 million, ``Never Been Kissed'' in 
fourth with $4.1 million, ``Analyze This'' in fifth with $2.2 
million and ``10 Things I Hate About You'' in sixth with $1.81 
million. 
</P>
<P>
	Led by ``The Matrix,'' April ended up as the first  
record-breaking month this year in box office take with more than 
$448.2 million. But the milestone was due to ticket price 
inflation, since admissions were actually down 2 percent from last 
year, when ``Titanic'' was still hot. 
</P>
<P>
	Among the duds were ``Lost and Found,'' which plummeted 59  
percent in its second week to finish eighth with $1.3 million, and 
``Pushing Tin,'' which suffered an even steeper 65 percent drop to 
finish ninth with $1.25 million. 
</P>
<P>
	``Go,'' another disappointment, rounded out the Top 10 with $1.2  
million. 
</P>
<P>
	The top 20 movies at North American theaters Friday through  
Sunday, followed by distributing studio, gross, number of theater 
locations, average receipts per location, total gross and number of 
weeks in release, as compiled by Exhibitor Relations Co. Inc. and 
ACNielsen EDI Inc.: 
</P>
<P>
	1. ``Entrapment,'' 20th Century Fox, $20.1 million, 2,815  
locations, $7,157 average, $20.1 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	2. ``The Matrix,'' Warner Bros., $8.7 million, 2,903 locations,  
$3,002 average, $129.7 million, five weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	3. ``Life,'' Universal, $6.5 million, 2,613 locations, $2,480  
average, $46.3 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	4. ``Never Been Kissed,'' Fox, $4.1 million, 2,481 locations,  
$1,641 average, $36.5 million, four weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	5. ``Analyze This,'' Warner Bros., $2.2 million, 2,128  
locations, $1,022 average, $98.5 million, nine weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	6. ``10 Things I Hate About You,'' Disney, $1.81 million, 2,020  
locations, $897 average, $31.1 million, five weeks. 
</P>
<P>
