<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dollar, Gold Rates Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was mixed against other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold also was mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	The big currency markets in London were closed for a holiday.  
</P>
<P>
	But other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Friday  
figures in London, showed that the euro was quoted at $1.0569, down 
from $1.0584, while the British pound rose to $1.6106, up from 
$1.6105 late Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	In New York at midday, the dollar was worth 120.21 yen and  
1.5218 Swiss francs. The euro was worth $1.0572 and the British 
pound was worth $1.6086. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe compared with late Friday in London  
included 119.89 Japanese yen, up from 119.58; 1.5236 Swiss francs, 
down from 1.5280; and 1.4565 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4583. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.8505 German marks, up from 1.8479; 
6.2064 French francs, up from 6.1970; and 1,832.03 Italian lire, up 
from 1,829.43 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price for gold was 286.05, down from $286.15  
late Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold rose 30 cents in Hong Kong to $286.45.  
</P>
<P>
	Metal markets in London were closed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
