<HEADLINE> 6 Reported Dead in Wichita Tornado </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Tornadoes ripped through south Wichita on  
Monday night, tossing mobile homes into a lake and damaging homes. 
At least six people were killed, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	One person died when a building collapsed in Wichita, the  
MidAmerica News Network reported. 
</P>
<P>
	Fred Irvin of the Sedgwick County Emergency Preparedness Office  
said multiple injuries were reported in Wichita and nearby 
Haysville. Irvin said six people were killed. 
</P>
<P>
	Several mobile homes in south Wichita were blown into a lake and  
several other homes were damaged, Irvin said. At least one of the 
fatalities was in the mobile home park, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Thirteen-year-old Courtney Karr said she saw the bay windows in  
her house cave in and the tornado swirling inside the house. She 
and her 15-year-old sister Jessie were trapped in the basement when 
their house was destroyed. 
</P>
<P>
	``I got hit in the head by a lawn chair,'' said Jessie.  
</P>
<P>
	Irvin said the storms, which included high winds and heavy  
rains, hit the area about 8:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	``It seems as if more than one tornado touched down,'' Irvin  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The county declared a state of local emergency disaster. Power  
lines and trees were reported down throughout the county. 
</P>
<P>
	A mobile home owned by Chad Harris was rolled over by the  
tornado with eight people inside. 
</P>
<P>
	``I have no trailer,'' Harris said. ``We all rolled in it. It  
was the worst experience in my life.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Two people in the trailer were in critical condition.  
</P>
</TEXT>
