<HEADLINE> Rockies Recall Sexton From Triple-A </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- The Colorado Rockies on Monday sent outfielder Pat  
Watkins to Triple-A Colorado Springs and recalled infielder Chris 
Sexton. 
</P>
<P>
	Watkins, acquired in a trade with Florida in March, cleared  
waivers before being outrighted to Colorado Springs. He was 
1-for-19 in 16 games with the Rockies. 
</P>
<P>
	Sexton, 27, has never played in the majors. He hit .340 with  
five runs and five RBIs for Colorado Springs this season. 
</P>
