<HEADLINE> Baseball Luxury Tax Payrolls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
        Baseball payrolls by average annual value as of opening day,  
compiled by the commissioner's office for luxury tax purposes, as obtained 
by The Associated Press: 
</P>
<P>
        Payrolls are for 40-man rosters and include averages of multiyear  
contracts plus $5,737,269 to cover health and pension benefits; clubs 
medical costs; insurance; workman's compensation, payroll, unemployment 
and Social Security taxes; spring training allowances; meal and tip 
money; All-Star game expenses; travel and moving expenses; postseason 
pay; and college scholarships. 
</P>
<P>
        The projected luxury tax is assessed at a rate of 34 percent  
on the amount above the midpoint between the fifth and sixth teams 
(currently $81,898,568) for the five teams with the highest payrolls. 
The actual luxury tax will be assessed on the final payroll after the 
season. 
