<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Williams, Smoltz Honored by NL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Matt Williams of the Arizona Diamondbacks and  
John Smoltz of the Atlanta Braves were honored Monday as the 
National League's player and pitcher of the month for April. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams batted .357 for the month with eight home runs and 25  
runs batted in. He had nine doubles and scored 18 runs. 
</P>
<P>
	Smoltz went 4-0 with a 1.51 earned run average for April. He  
struck out 34 batters in 35 2-3 innings. 
</P>
<P>
	Other candidates for the player award were Tony Gwynn of San  
Diego and Jeff Bagwell of Houston. Also nominated for the pitcher 
award were John Franco of the New York Mets and John Johnstone of 
San Francisco. 
</P>
