<HEADLINE> Tampa's Julio Santana Placed on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- The Tampa Bay Devil Rays placed  
pitcher Julio Santana on the 15-day disabled list Monday with right 
shoulder tendinitis and recalled pitcher Ryan Rupe from Double-A 
Orlando. 
</P>
<P>
	Santana reported nagging shoulder discomfort after starting  
Sunday's 8-2 loss to the Detroit Tigers. The right-hander allowed 
eight runs -- seven earned -- and 10 hits in five-plus innings. 
</P>
<P>
	Rupe, taken in the fifth round in last June's draft, becomes the  
first Tampa Bay draft pick to make the major league roster. The 
right-hander, who is scheduled to start Wednesday night's game 
against the Kansas City Royals, went 2-2 with 2.73 ERA in five 
games at Orlando. 
</P>
