<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Canseco Splits With Second Wife </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Jose Canseco of the Tampa Bay Devil Rays is  
divorcing his wife of less than three years. 
</P>
<P>
	Canseco, 34, and Jessica Marie, 26, have one child, Josie Marie,  
2 1/2. 
</P>
<P>
	According to their prenuptial agreement, Jessica agreed to a  
lump sum of $100,000 in lieu of alimony, The Miami Herald reported 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Canseco, who has been married twice, reportedly will give her an  
extra $100,000 for her promise to maintain a Florida residence 
until Josie turns 18. Jessica also wants child support. 
</P>
<P>
	He gets the 12,500-square-foot Weston home, on the market for  
$4.5 million. She gets the '97 BMW 740iL. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1997, police arrested Canseco and charged him with  
misdemeanor battery after he allegedly smacked Jessica in the head. 
He was ordered to undergo battery counseling. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1992, he was charged with aggravated assault for ramming his  
vehicle into a new car driven by his first wife. He agreed to 
community service and counseling. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
