<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> ANZ Buys Bank Papan Credit Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MELBOURNE, Australia (AP) -- ANZ Banking Group Ltd. said Monday  
that its Indonesian joint venture operation, PT ANZ Panin Bank, 
will acquire the credit card operations of PT Bank Papan Sejahtera. 
</P>
<P>
	The credit card operations will be purchased from the Indonesian  
Bank Restructuring Agency for $4.6 million, it said. 
</P>
<P>
	ANZ said Bank Papan's credit card business, with more than  
47,000 accounts, includes state-of-the-art technology platform 
consistent with ANZ's card operating platform, 
</P>
<P>
	The acquisition followed a tender conducted by the Indonesian  
Bank Restructuring Agency. 
</P>
<P>
	Bank Papan was one of 38 banks taken over by the Indonesian  
government in March 1999. 
</P>
<P>
	ANZ currently holds a 4.9 percent stake in Panin Bank,  
Indonesia's ninth largest private commercial bank, and an 85 
percent interest in the joint venture, PT ANZ Panin Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
