<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Texas Gas Leak Sends 65 To Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- A carbon monoxide leak at Continental Airlines'  
catering service sent about 65 people to the hospital early today 
with nausea and headaches. 
</P>
<P>
	The leak happened at Chelsea Catering Corp. at Bush  
Intercontinental Airport. Airport operations were not affected. 
</P>
<P>
	The catering company had been using portable generators because  
of a weekend power outage at the building, said Richard Fernandez, 
a spokesman for the agency that oversees Houston's airports. 
Exhaust from the generators apparently seeped into the building, he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Chelsea Catering is a Continental subsidiary that supplies meals  
to 12 airlines, including Continental. 
</P>
<P>
	Because the leak was expected to disrupt Monday's food service,  
Continental spokesman Dave Messing said the airline would provide 
passengers with meal vouchers that can be spent at the airport. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
