<HEADLINE> Bosox Catcher's First Hit Is Grand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Creighton Gubanich made the most of his  
first major league hit -- a grand slam Monday for the Boston Red Sox 
against the Oakland Athletics. 
</P>
<P>
	Gubanich, called up by the Red Sox on April 16 to replace  
injured catcher Scott Hatteberg, had only three major league 
at-bats -- a strikeout, a popout and an inning-ending double play 
grounder -- before starting Monday's game. 
</P>
<P>
	In the first inning, with Boston already leading 1-0, Gubanich  
hit a 3-and-2 pitch from Jimmy Haynes over the left-center fence. 
Gubanich pumped his right arm in the air as he rounded first base. 
</P>
