<HEADLINE> Marlins' Fernandez Missing 3 Weeks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Florida's Alex Fernandez will miss at least three  
weeks with a pulled groin, the latest setback in his comeback from 
shoulder surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	Fernandez, who missed the entire 1998 season following surgery  
to repair a torn rotator cuff, was placed on the 15-day disabled 
list Monday. The Marlins recalled reliever Rafael Medina from 
Triple-A Calgary. 
</P>
<P>
	Fernandez is on the DL for the second time in the last month.  
Earlier, he was out with inflammation in the surgically repaired 
shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
	Team physician Dan Kanell has said it's likely Fernandez will be  
out a minimum of three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's frustrating, but it's something I plan to take care of,''  
Fernandez said. 
</P>
<P>
	Fernandez said his shoulder felt fine in Sunday's 4-2 loss to  
the Astros. He injured his right groin muscle in the second inning. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's like there's a black cloud over us,'' said Marlins  
manager John Boles. 
</P>
<P>
	The Marlins have on off day Thursday, so they won't need another  
starter until May 11. The team will make a decision later in the 
week on who will move into the rotation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
