<HEADLINE> Circus Circus Proposing Name Change </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Circus Circus Enterprises Inc. is so pleased  
with the success of its new Mandalay Bay resort that it wants to 
rename the company after it. 
</P>
<P>
	The gambling company said Monday it will propose to shareholders  
that the company be renamed Mandalay Resort Group at its annual 
meeting in June. 
</P>
<P>
	The company revealed the new name at the same time it reported  
that its results for the quarter ending April 30 will significantly 
exceed the estimates of Wall Street analysts. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts expected earnings on an operating basis of about 25  
cents a share, while the company said it will be 40 cents to 42 
cents a share. 
</P>
<P>
	The news boosted Circus Circus shares in midday trading by about  
13.4 percent, as it rose $2.81 1/4 a share to $23.87 1/2. 
</P>
<P>
	Circus Circus said in a statement that a good start at Mandalay  
Bay, which opened in March, and strong occupancy rates and room 
rate increases at its other hotel-casinos led to a very good 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Circus Circus also reported it has authorized a share repurchase  
program for up to 15 percent of the company's outstanding shares. 
</P>
<P>
	Circus Circus owns and operates 11 properties in Nevada,  
including five on the Las Vegas Strip. It also has a hotel-casino 
in Mississippi and owns a half interest in a riverboat casino in 
Illinois. 

</P>
</TEXT>
