<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Kidd, Carter, Popovich Win Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Jason Kidd of the Phoenix Suns, Vice Carter of  
the Toronto Raptors and coach Gregg Popovich of the San Antonio 
Spurs are April's award winners in the NBA. 
</P>
<P>
	Kidd was picked as player of the month after accounting for more  
than 40 percent of the Suns' offense during the month as Phoenix 
qualified for the playoffs for the 11th consecutive season. He 
averaged 20.1 points, 10.4 assists, 6.7 rebounds and 2.38 steals 
during the month and had two triple-doubles, increasing his league 
lead to seven. 
</P>
<P>
	Carter, who led all first-year players in scoring and shot  
blocking during April, was chosen as rookie of the month. He 
averaged 20.6 points, 5.9 rebounds, 4.2 assists and 1.61 blocked 
shots. He was the fifth player chosen in last June's college draft. 
</P>
<P>
	Popovich's Spurs had the best record in the NBA for April at  
13-3 -- including 9-0 at home -- making him coach of the month. San 
Antonio began the lockout-abbreviated NBA season at 6-8 but has 
improved to 35-13, challenging the Utah Jazz for first place in the 
Midwest Division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
